why is my movable type installation not working after the www cgi server upgrade stanford answers stanford university stanford answers why is my movable type installation not working after the www cgi server upgrade categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home why is my movable type installation not working after the www cgi server upgrade search this site the upgrade of software affected certain libraries that were very dated on the old cgi servers the new servers cannot read the old movable type information without the data being converted to fix this log onto a solaris machine first such as tree stanford edu and do the following change to the db subdirectory of your movable type directory in most cases this would be cgi bin mt db mkdir bak cp idx db bak your sunet id public mt dump pl rm idx db exit then log on to a linux machine such as corn stanford edu change to the movable type db directory again your sunet id public mt load pl rm data exit finally go to your movable type page on the web log in and it will prompt you that an upgrade is pending click on the button to upgrade and then the system will run checks realize that you ve already done the needed job and inform you that everything has been set up at this point you should be able to access movable type as normal cgi stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
